	                        <div id="dsq-comment-message-2951867844" class="dsq-comment-message">
	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-2951867844" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>Hi Benson!</p><p>Welcome to Symfony! I can definitely help you with this - it's just one *small* thing :). In your route, you have `/employee/{employeeName}`. This means that you are allowed to have a `$employeeName` argument to your controller. But, you have `$employeeId`. Symfony is basically saying:</p><p>&gt; Hey! I see `$employeeId` as an argument to showAction(), but I don't see a {employeeId} in your route, so I don't know what value to pass here!</p><p>The fix is to make these match - probably in your case by changing the route to `/employee/{employeeId}`. Also, when you do this, if you have any links to this route (the employee_show route), you'll need to update those as well to now pass employeeId instead of employeeName (<a href="http://disq.us/url?url=http%3A%2F%2Fknpuniversity.com%2Fscreencast%2Fsymfony%2Furl-generation%23the-twig-path-function%29%3AnYlO-JDMWJZaPxJeCdN5Ycen8NM&amp;cuid=1175718" rel="nofollow noopener">http://knpuniversity.com/scree...</a>.</p><p>Let me know if this helps!</p><p>Cheers!</p>
	                            </div>
	                        </div>
	                    </div>
